Title: Suntec AS47C 7451 fuel pump
Description: This Suntec AS oil pump has a built-in normally opened solenoid valve for quick control of the cut-off and cut-on function independent of rotational speed. The pump's gear set draws oil from the tank through the built-in filter and transfers it to the valve that regulates the oil pressure to the nozzle line, dumping unused oil back to the return line in a two pipe installation or back to the suction port in a one pipe installation. When the solenoid valve is non-activated, the bypass channel between pressure and return sides is open, with no pressure built to open the valve. When the solenoid is activated, this bypass channel is closed and with gear set at full speed, the pressure necessary to open the valve will be built up for sharp cut-on.
